attributes

java.util.List<java.util.Set<A>> attributes()
Gets the list of properties. For each property, the element may have many values. If the object does not have any property, it returns null. The method List.get(int) returns an empty set if the provided index is valid but the element has no value for the corresponding attribute, or raises IndexOutOfBoundsException if the provided index is not valid.

Returns:
the list of properties, or null when the object does not have any property
Throws:
java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the provided index is not valid.
